# ── Normative citations ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

1  | cites   | :protocol, :http_sse_2024_11_05     | mcp-2024-11-05          | docs/references/mcp/mcp-transports-2024-11-05.md           |          | MCP specifies HTTP+SSE as a transport option and JSON-RPC as content grammar
2  | cites   | :content, :json_rpc                  | jsonrpc-2.0             | docs/references/jsonrpc/jsonrpc-2.0.md                     |          | JSON-RPC 2.0 defines request, response, notification, error message kinds
3  | cites   | :framing, :content_length            | rfc9110                 | docs/references/rfcs/rfc9110-http-semantics.txt            | 8.6      | Content-Length header defines request body framing (client→server POST direction)
4  | cites   | :transport, :sse                     | whatwg-html-sse         | docs/references/rfcs/server-sent-events-whatwg.md           |          | SSE defines server→client event stream framing (empty-line delimited events)
5  | cites   | :dimension, :session_id              | rfc4122                 |                                                            |          | UUID format per RFC 4122; SDK uses uuid4
6  | cites   | :jsonrpc_request                     | jsonrpc-2.0             | docs/references/jsonrpc/jsonrpc-2.0.md                     |          | Request object has method, params, and id fields
7  | cites   | :jsonrpc_response                    | jsonrpc-2.0             | docs/references/jsonrpc/jsonrpc-2.0.md                     |          | Response object has either result OR error, plus id
8  | cites   | :jsonrpc_error                       | jsonrpc-2.0             | docs/references/jsonrpc/jsonrpc-2.0.md                     |          | Error object has code, message, and optional data
9  | cites   | :jsonrpc_notification                | jsonrpc-2.0             | docs/references/jsonrpc/jsonrpc-2.0.md                     |          | Notification is a Request WITHOUT an id field — field absent, not null
10 | cites   | :create_session                      | python-sdk              | docs/references/mcp/python-sdk-sse-transport.md            |          | SDK generates uuid4 per GET /sse connection; session_id routes POSTs
11 | cites   | :destroy_session                     | python-sdk              | docs/references/mcp/python-sdk-sse-transport.md            |          | SDK removes session from dict when SSE stream context manager exits
12 | cites   | :http_404_response                   | python-sdk              | docs/references/mcp/python-sdk-sse-transport.md            |          | SDK returns 404 "Could not find session" for unknown session_id

